Political mobilisation is rapidly taking shape in the country as we embark on Constitutional amendment, a culmination of a handshake between two leading political protagonists, President Kenyatta and ODM leader Raila Odinga.
This is expected to get a notch higher as the country draws towards the 2022 General Election. Lamentably, young people, a massive political constituency in its own right, by virtue of its huge number, are yet to take a collective and organised action to at least ensure they take more leadership positions.



